message:
@alex how do I pass to gcc-4.0 the postgresql's include path and lib path?  

When compiling, pypy-postgresql, I am getting this error http://dpaste.com/562119/ telling me that libpq-fe.h cannot be found.  This is not correct as I know for certain by going to my /opt/local/include/postgresql90 that libpq-fe.h exist and /opt/local/lib/postgresql is the path to my postgresql90 libraries.

Is it possible to specify an option when running translate.py so that the compilation process takes in my macports path to postgresql related header file and libraries?
